
nslookup is a network administration command-line tool used to query Domain Name System (DNS) to obtain domain name or IP address mapping.


-- Command	Description	-- 

nslookup example.com	
Basic domain lookup to find the A record (IP address) of a domain	
nslookup google.com

nslookup 192.168.1.1	
Reverse DNS lookup to find the domain name of an IP address	nslookup 
8.8.8.8

nslookup example.com 8.8.8.8	
Query a specific DNS server for domain information	
nslookup google.com 8.8.8.8

nslookup -type=mx example.com	
Query MX (Mail Exchange) records for a domain	
nslookup -type=mx gmail.com

nslookup -type=ns example.com	
Query NS (Name Server) records for a domain	
nslookup -type=ns example.com

nslookup -type=txt example.com	
Query TXT (Text) records (e.g., SPF, DKIM) for a domain	
nslookup -type=txt google.com

nslookup -type=soa example.com	
Query SOA (Start of Authority) record for a domain	
nslookup -type=soa example.com

nslookup -type=cname example.com	
Query CNAME (Canonical Name) records for alias domains	
nslookup -type=cname www.example.com

nslookup -type=a example.com	
Query the A record (IPv4 address) for a domain	
nslookup -type=a example.com
